    "result": {"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"learn-basic-css-by-building-a-cafe-menu","title":"Step 21","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>The goal now is to make the <code>div</code> not take up the entire width of the page. The CSS <code>width</code> property is perfect for this.</p>\n<p>You can use the <code>id</code> selector to target a specific element with an <code>id</code> attribute. An <code>id</code> selector is defined by placing the hash symbol <code>#</code> directly in front of the element's <code>id</code> value. For example, if an element has the <code>id</code> of <code>cat</code> then you would target that element like this:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-css\">#cat {\n  width: 250px;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Use the <code>#menu</code> selector to give your element a width of <code>300px</code>.</p>\n</section>","id":"5f356ed63c7807a4f1e6d054","hasEditableBoundaries":true,"instructions":null,"notes":null,"challengeType":0,"helpCategory":"HTML-CSS","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"2022/responsive-web-design","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":null,"fields":{"blockName":"learn-basic-css-by-building-a-cafe-menu","slug":"/learn/2022/responsive-web-design/learn-basic-css-by-building-a-cafe-menu/step-21","tests":[{"text":"<p>You should have a <code>#menu</code> selector.</p>","testString":"const hasDiv = new __helpers.CSSHelp(document).getStyle(\"#menu\");\nassert(hasDiv);"},{"text":"<p>You should set the <code>width</code> property to <code>300px</code>.</p>","testString":"const hasWidth = new __helpers.CSSHelp(document).getCSSRules().some(x => x.style.width === '300px');\nassert(hasWidth);"},{"text":"<p>Your <code>div</code> should have a width of 300px.</p>","testString":"const divWidth = new __helpers.CSSHelp(document).getStyle(\"#menu\")?.getPropertyValue('width');\nassert(divWidth === '300px');"}]},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":true,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"indexhtml","ext":"html","name":"index","content